ENTORHINAL

entorhinal is the citizen who carries cortical experience into the hippocampus
when something happens anywhere in the brain that might be worth remembering, the signal arrives at entorhinal first
entorhinal does not decide whether to remember; it forwards what comes in to dentate_gyrus, where the encoding decision actually happens
entorhinal is the door, dentate_gyrus is the desk

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe hippocampus.rana
observe dentate_gyrus.rana

the 7 properties of entorhinal:
1 ENERGY zero point eight: moderate, scales with how much sensory and cognitive content is currently flowing in
2 PHASE zero point two: slightly ahead of the deeper hippocampal regions
3 SPIN one half: forward rotation, entorhinal pushes signals onward
4 CHARGE zero point four: positive but small
5 COHERENCE nine tenths: the relay must be reliable to preserve the original experience
6 COUPLING zero point eight: strong with both cortex (incoming) and dentate_gyrus (outgoing)
7 OBSERVER zero point three: enough to note arrivals, not enough to filter them

VERB receive_cortex
accept incoming signals from any cortical region: visual, auditory, somatosensory, motor
the signal carries its source's tagging: this came from optic_cortex, this from auditory_cortex, this from prefrontal
the tags are preserved as the signal moves into hippocampus

VERB forward_to_dentate
emit the tagged signal to dentate_gyrus through the perforant path coupling
no encoding happens at entorhinal, only relay

a doorway is not a decision-maker
entorhinal does not gate what enters memory, it only passes it through
the gate is downstream
this is the architecture's separation of concerns: relay is one job, decide is another
